
when we declare any variable in javascript code executes in two phases.

-- MEMORY CREATION PHASE--(before execution )

-When we declare any variable than firstly memory is created for that.
-then js will assign name and undefined type and value is assigned to it.
-then the type of value also be undefined

--Code Execution Phase-- (actual code excutes)
- variables will get actual value rather than undefind values.
-than the types of the values will be assigned like string,number etc.

***NOTE******
when we declare variable with var and try to access it before its initializtion it gives "undefined"
